Generation pipeline (this run):
  - Architect override applied: Midjourney via Chrome MCP, NOT DALL-E
  - MJ v7, --stylize 1000, --ar 3:4, --no outlines text words letters
    photorealistic uncanny
  - Style anchor verbatim: "ukiyo-e woodblock print style, paper-texture
    background, fine ink-line definition, washed muted color palette,
    eastern folk-horror atmosphere"
  - 1 grid (4 panels) per asset, no rerolls needed — strongest panel
    matched the dominant register on first try.

Style register decision:
  - Pre-existing 7 split into TWO registers: lantern_acolyte and
    sigil_student carry a magenta-strip / illustrated cartoon look;
    the other 5 (horned_oni / paper_priest / silent_seer / scythe_widow /
    ash_brawler) carry the dominant ukiyo-e woodblock register with
    paper-texture + red Asian seal cartouches.
  - Decision: match the DOMINANT 5 (woodblock register) for the 2 new
    portraits, since a 7-of-9 consistent register is stronger than
    matching the 2-of-9 minority. Skipped magenta strip pipeline — the
    dominant 5 don't use it; the prompt produces full-bleed paper
    texture directly.
  - fox_kabuki: blue kimono, fox mask pushed up to forehead, painted lips
    visible, mysterious downcast expression. Red seal cartouche bottom-left
    + top-right. Reads as the same artist's hand as silent_seer and
    scythe_widow.
  - cap_apprentice: young messenger in conical straw hat tilted forward
    obscuring eyes, blue traveling robe, walking staff in hand, full
    backpack with bedroll. Calligraphy + red seal upper-right + red seal
    lower-left. Reads as the same hand as horned_oni / ash_brawler.

Download workflow notes (institutional memory):
  - MJ menu "Download Image" worked first time (fox_kabuki) but silently
    failed on subsequent click for cap_apprentice — possibly Chrome MCP
    automation suppression or per-session quirk.
  - Workaround: opened the direct CDN URL
    (https://cdn.midjourney.com/<jobId>/0_0.jpeg) in a new tab → fetched
    same-origin via JS → created a Blob URL → clicked anchor with
    download attribute. Saved cleanly. Worth recording for next worker
    if MJ menu download stops cooperating.
  - Direct curl with cookies-from-browser was not attempted because
    Chrome MCP blocks cookie reads.

